Christianity is the predominant religion in Europe, the Americas and Southern Africa. In Asia, it is the dominant religion in Georgia, Armenia, East Timor and the Philippines.[196] However, it is declining in many areas including the Northern and Western United States,[197] Oceania (Australia and New Zealand), northern Europe (including Great Britain,[198] Scandinavia and other places), France, Germany, the Canadian provinces of Ontario, British Columbia, and Quebec, and parts of Asia (especially the Middle East â€“ due to the Christian emigration,[199][200][201] South Korea,[202] Taiwan,[203] and Macau[204]).
